text: James Franklin Wiley was a member of the Wisconsin State Senate. ==Biography== Wiley was born on May 17, 1832 in Gouverneur, New York. He died on January 12, 1902 and was buried in Hancock, Wisconsin. ==Career== Wiley represented the 9th District in the Senate. Other positions he held include Postmaster of Hancock.
